<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,580,838]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
<bibRefCitation author="Barroso, G. M." box="[151,329,580,606]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 281" refId="ref6519" refString="Barroso, G. M. (1976) Subtribo Baccharidinae Hoffman. Estudo das especies ocorrentes no Brasil. Rodriguesia 28: 1 - 281." type="journal article" year="1976">Barroso (1976)</bibRefCitation>
only indicated 
<emphasis box="[511,670,580,605]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Sellow d2013</emphasis>
as “ 
<typeStatus box="[719,827,580,606]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">holotype</typeStatus>
” of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Candolle" authorityYear="1836" box="[877,1079,580,605]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="helichrysoides">
<emphasis box="[877,1079,580,605]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">B. helichrysoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, without citing any herbarium acronym. Although effectively a lectotypification, her choice was superseded owing to a previous lectotypification by 
<bibRefCitation author="Malagarriga Heras, R. P. &amp; Irmao Teodoro Luis" box="[395,630,657,683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 61" refId="ref7201" refString="Malagarriga Heras, R. P. [as Irmao Teodoro Luis] (1957) Para o estudo da Flora Sul-Riograndense qual o valor da &quot; Flora Brasiliensis &quot; de Martius? Contribuicoes do Instituto Geobiologico La Salle 8: 1 - 61." type="journal article" year="1957">Malagarriga (1957)</bibRefCitation>
based on the same material in P. The 
<typeStatus box="[1093,1197,657,683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gardner" authorityYear="1848" box="[1240,1407,657,682]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanuginosa">
<emphasis box="[1240,1407,657,682]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">B. lanuginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is stated as being from 
<date box="[409,607,696,722]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" value="1840-09">September 1840</date>
on the type specimen sheet. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, G." box="[1091,1280,696,722]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" pagination="78 - 90" refId="ref6716" refString="Gardner, G. (1848) Contributions towards a Flora of Brazil, being the distinctive characters of some new species of Compositae, belonging to the tribe Asteroideae. The London journal of botany: containing figures and descriptions of such plants as recommend themselves by their novelty, rarity, history, or uses: together with botanical notices and information and occasional portraits and memoirs of eminent botanists 7: 78 - 90." type="journal article" year="1848">Gardner (1848)</bibRefCitation>
wrote ‘ 
<date pageId="2" pageNumber="43" value="1840-08">Aug. 1840</date>
’ in the protologue and cited the collection as ‘4900,1’. In the ‘Catalogue’ of his collections, the entry of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gardner" authorityYear="1848" box="[151,317,774,799]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanuginosa">
<emphasis box="[151,317,774,799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">B. lanuginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was clearly added relatively late when Gardner realized he had a ‘new species’ (Hind, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
